col2:'Our short film "Hello to the fjords!" wins the Fondo Metropolitano de Cultura, las Artes y las Ciencias.',t_novedades_col3:"The project will receive support to complete the postproduction stage and will be premiered at 18 Bafici Official competition.",t_about_us_description:"CIUDADES SUBTERRÁNEAS is a production company based in Buenos Aires. The house arouse in 2016 from Juan Bobbio and Alex Piperno´s desire to direct self-produced films and offer quality production services for advertising and other audiovisual pieces.",t_alex_bio:"Alex Piperno was born in Montevideo and lives in Buenos Aires since 2006.<br><br>He studied at the Universidad del Cine of Buenos Aires. He directed the short films THE INVIOLABILITY OF THE DOMICILE IS BASED ON THE MAN WHO APPEARS WIELDING AN AX AT THE DOOR OF HIS HOUSE, premiered at Cannes Critics' Week, HELLO TO THE FJORDS!, supported by the Metropolitan Fund and premiered at Bafici, and THE ZEBUS, currently in postproduction.<br><br>His feature film project WINDOW BOY WOULD ALSO LIKE TO HAVE A SUBMARINE, set to shoot in 2016, is supported by recognized festivals and international funds as Bafici Bal, San Sebastián Coproduction Forum, Berlinale Scripstation, BrLab, Binger Lab, Hubert Bals Fund, Ibermedia Fund for Development and Coproduction and Icau-Ancine Coproduction Fund, among others. <br><br> Coproducer of PARABELLUM, by Lukas V. Rinner, premiered at Rotterdam International Film Festival and awarded at Diagonale and Jeonju. <br><br> Residing alternately in Montevideo and Buenos Aires takes him to establish the production houses LA POBLADORA CINE and CIUDADES SUBTERRÁNEAS on either side of the river.",t_juan_bio:"Juan was born in Buenos Aires, where he is actually located. <br><br> He studied at the National Art University of Argentina.<br><br>His short films THE DEMOCRAT and THE LEAK have been selected in more than 30 international film festivals in countries such as United States, Mexico, Guatemala, Chile, Argentina, Spain, Morocco, Romain and Finland.<br><br>Was selected during BAFICI to participate at the 6th edition of Buenos Aires Talents.<br><br>Has directed advertisement, corporate pieces and music videos.<br><br>Actually he is developing his feature film THE KILLERS AGE and post­producing his third short film, THE FEVER AWAITS AWAKENING.",t_pelicula_derrames:"<strong>Technical information</strong> <br> Running time: 4 min<br> Genre: Experimental<br> Shooting format: HD / eFound footage<br> Screening format: DCP<br> Origin: Argentina<br> Year of production: 2011<br><br> <strong>Synopsis</strong><br> A worker is trapped by a technical fault in a maritime oil-drilling platform <br> <br> <strong>Cast</strong><br> Patricio Alvarado Plaza<br> Soledad Franchini <br><br> <strong>Crew </strong><br> Script writer and director: Juan Bobbio<br> Production companies: Ciuades subterráneas / La conciencia films<br> Cinematographer: Laura Molteni / Anna Pantano <br> Editor: Juan Bobbio<br> Music by: Federico Grinbank <br><br> <strong>Supports</strong><br> - Fondo Metropolitano de la Cultura, las Artes y las Ciencias del Ministerio de Cultura de GCBA. <br><br> <strong>Festivals and awards</strong> <br> - Competencia oficial 16vo Festival Ícaro, Guatemala, 2013 <br> - Competencia oficial Festival de Cortos Penca, Argentina, 2013 <br> - Screening program, 8vo CeC Carnival of e-Creativity, India, 2013 <br> - Competencia oficial Once a Week Online Film Festival, USA, 2013 <br> - Competencia oficial Festifreak, Argentina, 2012 - Primera mención categoría ficción. <br> - Screening program international film festival Visions of the world, Finlandia, 2012 <br> - Competencia oficial 4to Fórmula Mundi Film Fest, Egipto, 2012 – Tercer premio categoría experimental. <br> - Competencia oficial FLAVIA, Argentina, 2012 <br> - Competencia oficial FECIPA, Chile, 2012. <br> - Screening program festival internacional Espacio Enter, España, 2012. <br> - Competencia oficial 3er FIDBA, Argentina, 2012.",t_pelicula